headline: Supply Chain Challenges Could Cost Airlines More Than $11 Billion in 2025
summary: NEW YORK, October 13, 2025--Oliver Wyman, a global leader in management consulting and a business of Marsh McLennan (NYSE:MMC), today launched a joint study in collaboration with the International Air Transport Association (IATA). The report, Reviving the Commercial Aircraft Supply Chain, addresses supply chain challenges in the aerospace industry, and explores the root cause of these challenges, the impact on airlines, and initiatives to move the aviation industry forward.
